WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Land_O_Mines' is a Workbench game played on a 10 by 10 board
where a number of mines are placed randomly. You have to get to
the exit, which is located on the bottom of the board, without
stepping on a mine.

  You play by clicking on a tile adjacent to your position. You
can move horizontally, vertically or diagonally, and each time you
leave a tile, that tile disappears, so you cannot go back there.
Be careful not to 'trap' yourself on a tile with no other tiles
you can go to, in which case the game will be over.

  If one (or more) mine is adjacent to your position, all the
surrounding tiles (except the removed ones) will be marked by
a '?' icon, but you will never know exactly where the mine is
located.

  When you complete a level, the game counts how many moves you
made and multiply it by the bonus for that level, so the more
moves you make, the higher the score you will get. That score will
be added to the total score in the game. But if you step on a mine
(or trap yourself) only the number of moves will be added to the
total score.

  How far can you go? Is it better to make more moves (and get
more points) at the risk of stepping on a mine? Only you know the
answer!

  Have fun!

